iff).`\n3923\t\n3924\t- **Files added** (1):\n3925\t  - `peek/src/server/mutations/__tests__/runner.test.ts` — 11 tests\n3926\t    covering the FR-14 framework end to end with mocked `Sql`,\n3927\t    audit writer, action rules, and registry. No DB or network I/O.\n3928\t\n3929\t- **Test plan vs. checklist clauses**:\n3930\t  - **authorized success**: 3 tests\n3931\t    - \"runs execute inside a transaction and emits peek.change.applied\"\n3932\t      verifies `sql.begin` is called once, `executeFn` receives the\n3933\t      parsed input + transactional `Sql` + actor, the result carries\n3934\t      `actionId/resourceId/changes`, and the single audit emit is\n3935\t      `peek.change.applied` on the *transactional* sql (so the change\n3936\t      and its audit row commit/rollback together).\n3937\t    - \"populates the applied payload with FR-14 fields and forwards\n3938\t      the before/after diff\" pins every required `PeekAuditPayload`\n3939\t      field and confirms `changes` round-trip from execute.\n3940\t    - \"supports null resourceId / null changes (pure create)\"\n3941\t      covers the create-shaped mutation contract.\n3942\t  - **unauthorized denial**: 2 tests — role mismatch + null role.\n3943\t    Both confirm `sql.begin` is NOT called, no `executeFn` call, and\n3944\t    that `peek.change.rejected` is written on the **main** sql (not\n3945\t    a transactional one — there is no transaction yet).\n3946\t  - **validation failure**: 2 tests — invalid input rejected with\n3947\t    field errors surfaced to the caller; second test passes a\n3948\t    JWT-shaped smuggled value and proves the runner does not echo\n3949\t    raw input or field-level errors into the audit `changes` array\n3950\t    (FR-14 \"no submitted secrets\").\n3951\t  - **transaction rollback (execution_failed)**: 1 test — execute\n3952\t    throws, `sqlMock.rolledBack` is true, runner returns\n3953\t    `{ ok: false, reason: \"execution_failed\" }` with the underlying\n3954\t    error