Create` returns\n4026\t    `[{wallet, before:null, after}, {rate_bps, before:null, after}]`\n4027\t    so the audit row carries full new-state context for inserts.\n4028\t    `diffForUpdate` only includes fields whose values actually\n4029\t    changed (no spurious `set_by`/`updated_at` rows). The runner\n4030\t    serializes this list into `peek.change.applied.changes`.\n4031\t  - **\"rate validation\"** — `kolRateUpdateInputSchema` enforces\n4032\t    `z.number().int().min(0).max(10_000)`; invalid values short-circuit\n4033\t    to `peek.change.rejected` with `rejectionReason=\"invalid_input\"`\n4034\t    via the runner's existing schema-validation path. `userId` and\n4035\t    `wallet` are also trimmed and required.\n4036\t  - **\"set_by reflects the actor\"** — `set_by` is server-set to\n4037\t    `actor.email` (verified Cloudflare email from the runner's actor\n4038\t    context) and is intentionally excluded from the audit diff: it is\n4039\t    operator metadata, not user-facing config.\n4040\t\n4041\t- **Targeted checks** (CLAUDE.md TS rule):\n4042\t  - `cd peek && pnpm lint` ✅\n4043\t  - `cd peek && pnpm typecheck` ✅\n4044\t  - `cd peek && pnpm test --run` ✅ (79 files, 886/886 — no\n4045\t    regressions; the runner test file already covers this mutation\n4046\t    shape via local test factories, so the registry entry does not\n4047\t    perturb any existing assertion. Dedicated mutation tests land in\n4048\t    the next iteration \"[test] KOL rate mutation tests\").\n4049\t\n4050\t- **Next**: `[test] KOL rate mutation tests: create, update, invalid\n4051\t  rate, unauthorized actor, audit payload.`\n4052\t## Iteration 145 — 2026-04-26T15:25:36Z — OK\n4053\t- **Log**: iteration-145.log"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4de5a64f-41df-4f36-abe8-b663a1d849a0","uuid":"1023fa9a-34b4-440b-b50f-913ef56b9f27","timestamp":"2026-04-26T15:26:00.447Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/305-peek-operations-ad